env PAGER=cat man timing_report_constraint_report_all_drv_violatio n
Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_report..._drv_violation(25.10)    timing_report..._drv_violation(25.10)

Name
       timing_report_constraint_report_all_drv_violation

Syntax
       timing_report_constraint_report_all_drv_violation {true | false}

       Default: true

       Enables reporting of all the design rule violations (DRV).

       When  set  to false, the software reports the worst 1000 DRV violations
       per DRV check  (specified  with  the  report_constraint  -all_violators
       -drv_violation_type command).

       When  set to true, the software will report all the DRV violations. You
       can use the report_constraint -max_pins_per_drv  parameter  to  specify
       the maximum number of DRV violations to be reported.

       Note:  The  -max_pins_per_drv  parameter has higher precedence over the
       timing_report_constraint_report_all_drv_violation global variable  set-
       ting.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

